---
/*
  Comments + reactions via Giscus (GitHub Discussions).
  SETUP (5 minutes, one time):
  1. Push this repo to GitHub and make it public (or use a separate public repo just for comments).
  2. Enable "Discussions" in the repo settings.
  3. Install the Giscus app: https://github.com/apps/giscus
  4. Go to https://giscus.app — pick your repo, category "Announcements",
     mapping "pathname", enable reactions.
  5. Copy the generated data-repo, data-repo-id, data-category and
     data-category-id values into the script tag below, then remove the
     `hidden` attribute from the section.
*/
---
<section class="comments" hidden>
  <h2>Comments</h2>
  <script
    src="https://giscus.app/client.js"
    data-repo="YOUR_GITHUB_USER/YOUR_REPO"
    data-repo-id="REPLACE_ME"
    data-category="Announcements"
    data-category-id="REPLACE_ME"
    data-mapping="pathname"
    data-strict="0"
    data-reactions-enabled="1"
    data-emit-metadata="0"
    data-input-position="top"
    data-theme="light"
    data-lang="en"
    crossorigin="anonymous"
    async
  ></script>
</section>
